# The `SmallPtrSetImpl` Class Template Reference

<DoxygenPage pluginConfig={pluginConfig}>

A templated base class for <code><a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/smallptrset">SmallPtrSet</a></code> which provides the typesafe interface that is common across all small sizes. <a href="#details">More...</a>

## Declaration

<CodeBlock>template &lt;typename PtrType&gt;
class llvm::SmallPtrSetImpl&lt;PtrType&gt;</CodeBlock>

## Description {#details}

A templated base class for <code><a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/smallptrset">SmallPtrSet</a></code> which provides the typesafe interface that is common across all small sizes.

This is particularly useful for passing around between interface boundaries to avoid encoding a particular small size in the interface boundary.

Definition at line 363 of file <a href="/docs/api/files/include/include/llvm/include/llvm/adt/smallptrset-h">SmallPtrSet.h</a>.

Remove pointer from the set.

Returns whether the pointer was in the set. Invalidates iterators if true is returned. To remove elements while iterating over the set, use <a href="#a4323c151516742793df95050739d72ab">remove&#95;if()</a> instead.

  labels = {["inline"]}>
Inserts Ptr if and only if there is no element in the container equal to Ptr.

The bool component of the returned pair is true if and only if the insertion takes place, and the iterator component of the pair points to the element equal to Ptr.

### remove&#95;if() {#a4323c151516742793df95050739d72ab}

<MemberDefinition
  template={<>template &lt;typename UnaryPredicate&gt;</>}
  prototype={<>bool llvm::SmallPtrSetImpl&lt; PtrType &gt;::remove&#95;if (UnaryPredicate P)</>}
  labels = {["inline"]}>
Remove elements that match the given predicate.

This method is a safe replacement for the following pattern, which is not valid, because the <a href="#a11045c7973ab24a8d6315b61fa337d4e">erase()</a> calls would invalidate the iterator: <CodeBlock>for (PtrType &#42;Ptr : Set)
  if (Pred(P))
    Set.erase(P);
</CodeBlock>

Returns whether anything was removed. It is safe to read the set inside the predicate function. However, the predicate must not modify the set itself, only indicate a removal by returning true.

Definition at line <a href="/docs/api/files/include/include/llvm/include/llvm/adt/smallptrset-h/#l00418">418</a> of file <a href="/docs/api/files/include/include/llvm/include/llvm/adt/smallptrset-h">SmallPtrSet.h</a>.
</MemberDefinition>
